questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-volume Spring Boot application deployed on an embedded Tomcat container slowly degrades in performance over several days. GC logs reveal that Major GCs are occurring with increasing frequency, and the Tenured (Old) generation memory usage never drops back to its baseline, eventually triggering `OutOfMemoryError`. You find the following Filter responsible for tracking user sessions:

java
@Component
public class UserContextFilter implements Filter {
    private static final ThreadLocal<UserContext> contextHolder = new ThreadLocal<>();

    @Override
    public void doFilter(ServletRequest request, ServletResponse response, FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException {
        UserContext context = extractContext(request);
        contextHolder.set(context);
        chain.doFilter(request, response);
    }
}
